254
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:06,468
entertainments,
private office staff...

255
00:14:06,639 --> 00:14:09,358
- Duplicating machines...
- Yes. Yes. Yes. Fine. Yes.

256
00:14:09,519 --> 00:14:11,430
That's where we'll start.

257
00:14:11,599 --> 00:14:14,432
- Unfortunately there is a difficulty.
- I knew it!

258
00:14:14,599 --> 00:14:16,430
It does cause
profound resentment

259
00:14:16,599 --> 00:14:19,557
if those at the top continue
to enjoy the comforts

260
00:14:19,719 --> 00:14:21,675
they withdraw
from those below them,

261
00:14:21,839 --> 00:14:24,478
not to mention
the deeply damaging publicity...

262
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:27,876
You mean you and I should...

263
00:14:28,079 --> 00:14:29,797
Set a personal example?

264
00:14:30,039 --> 00:14:31,711
Economy begins at home?

265
00:14:31,879 --> 00:14:35,315
We can't expect others to do
whatwe don't do ourselves, can we?

266
00:14:36,599 --> 00:14:39,557
- Would it really save all that much?
- Well, not directly, no.

267
00:14:39,719 --> 00:14:44,634
But, as an example to the whole
public service... incalculable.

268
00:14:44,879 --> 00:14:46,198
Well, I don't know...

269
00:14:46,359 --> 00:14:49,635
Jim, there'd be
a lot of great publicity in it:

270
00:14:50,679 --> 00:14:52,749
"The Ministershows the way".

271
00:14:53,159 --> 00:14:54,797
"Slimline Government".

272
00:14:54,959 --> 00:14:58,269
"Hackersets an example".
"Save it" says Jim.

273
00:14:58,439 --> 00:14:59,997
Yes. Yes, that's it.

274
00:15:00,239 --> 00:15:01,991
Great, where do we start?

275
00:15:08,519 --> 00:15:11,352
- Oh! Turn the...
- Sorry. Were you asleep?

276
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:12,519
Yes.

277
00:15:14,119 --> 00:15:15,518
I missed my train.

278
00:15:15,879 --> 00:15:17,710
Had to walk all the way to Euston.

279
00:15:17,879 --> 00:15:20,393
- And the chauffeurdriven car?
- Got rid of it.

280
00:15:20,559 --> 00:15:24,029
Got rid of the chauffeurtoo,
and all that office furniture,

281
00:15:24,199 --> 00:15:27,032
drinks cabinet, half the staff
in my private office.

282
00:15:30,199 --> 00:15:32,349
- You've been sacked.
- No, no...

283
00:15:33,519 --> 00:15:35,794
- Then why?
- It's an economy drive.

284
00:15:35,959 --> 00:15:39,952
I'm setting an example.
No luxuries, no frills, no privileges...

285
00:15:40,319 --> 00:15:41,638
You're mad...

286
00:15:41,879 --> 00:15:45,588
For 20 years you've complained
you had no facilities.

287
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:48,273
- Now you're throwing them away.
- But, darling...

288
00:15:48,439 --> 00:15:50,907
20 years you've wanted
to be a success.

289
00:15:51,079 --> 00:15:54,071
Why, if it brings no greater
comfort than failure?

290
00:15:54,239 --> 00:15:56,150
You don't really understand
politics.

291
00:15:56,319 --> 00:15:59,709
This way it's going to bring me
much more power in the end.

292
00:15:59,879 --> 00:16:03,554
And how are you going to travel
when you are Prime Minister.

293
00:16:03,719 --> 00:16:04,993
Hitch hike?

294
00:16:13,199 --> 00:16:16,794
- Bernard, ourdiary session.
- As soon as I've done this typing.

295
00:16:17,159 --> 00:16:19,992
- Can't you get...?
- Not really, it's ratherurgent.

296
00:16:20,159 --> 00:16:23,276
And since the cutbacks
there's just the two of us.

297
00:16:23,439 --> 00:16:25,157
Well, I must talk to you.

