00:20:07,319 --> 00:20:08,832
Sorry to keep you.

371
00:20:09,159 --> 00:20:12,310
Now, about yourappointment.
When would be convenient...

372
00:20:12,479 --> 00:20:14,947
- The meeting's cancelled then?
- Yes.

373
00:20:15,119 --> 00:20:18,236
- So I can see him now?
- I'm afraid not, you see...

374
00:20:18,399 --> 00:20:20,355
Would you excuse me
just a moment?

375
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:23,468
Yes?
No. He's not here.

376
00:20:24,199 --> 00:20:28,511
He's gone overto the Whips Office.
Would you like the extension?

377
00:20:30,359 --> 00:20:32,668
Ah, Mr...

378
00:20:33,439 --> 00:20:34,439
Brough?

379
00:20:34,599 --> 00:20:36,874
Mr. Brough's
had to cancel the meeting.

380
00:20:37,039 --> 00:20:38,711
My name's Ron Watson. I'm...

381
00:20:38,879 --> 00:20:40,915
I'm glad
you could get here instead.

382
00:20:41,079 --> 00:20:43,309
- Do sit down, won't you.
- Oh, thank you.

383
00:20:43,479 --> 00:20:44,878
Now, Mr. Er...

384
00:20:45,039 --> 00:20:46,267
Watson.

385
00:20:46,479 --> 00:20:50,552
Before we start there's one thing
I must make absolutely clear.

386
00:20:50,719 --> 00:20:52,550
This must not get out.

387
00:20:53,199 --> 00:20:55,633
If the unions
were to get to hearof this

388
00:20:56,639 --> 00:20:58,834
all hell would be let loose.

389
00:20:59,319 --> 00:21:00,513
Oh, yes.

390
00:21:01,079 --> 00:21:04,355
Of course there'll be redundancies.
You simply...

391
00:21:04,519 --> 00:21:06,953
You simply can't slim down

392
00:21:07,119 --> 00:21:10,429
a giant bureaucracy like this
without getting rid of people.

393
00:21:10,719 --> 00:21:12,516
Ultimately, a lot of people.

394
00:21:12,679 --> 00:21:15,716
Won't you be holding discussions
with the Unions first?

395
00:21:15,879 --> 00:21:17,835
We'll go through
the charade of discussions,

396
00:21:17,999 --> 00:21:20,069
but you know
what Trade Unionists are like;

397
00:21:20,239 --> 00:21:22,548
thick as two short planks
and bloody minded.

398
00:21:24,439 --> 00:21:25,554
All of them?

399
00:21:25,719 --> 00:21:28,279
Pretty well.
Good lord, you should know.

400
00:21:28,439 --> 00:21:31,112
They're interested in poaching
each other's members

401
00:21:31,279 --> 00:21:33,668
and they can't keep
theirbig mouths shut.

402
00:21:34,639 --> 00:21:38,188
What about drivers
and transport service staff?

403
00:21:38,359 --> 00:21:39,394
First to go.

404
00:21:39,559 --> 00:21:42,027
We waste a fortuna
on cars and drivers.

405
00:21:42,199 --> 00:21:45,316
- And they're all on the fiddle.
- Oh, I see.

406
00:21:46,159 --> 00:21:50,630
Because, as I was trying to explain,
I'm not Mr. Brough's deputy.

407
00:21:51,079 --> 00:21:55,311
I'm the General Secretary of the Union
of Civil Service Transport

408
00:21:55,479 --> 00:21:57,788
and Associated Government Workers.

409
00:21:58,919 --> 00:21:59,919
Ah. I...

410
00:22:00,079 --> 00:22:02,718
I came here to check there was
no truth in the rumours

411
00:22:02,879 --> 00:22:04,949
of redundancies formy members.

412
00:22:05,519 --> 00:22:07,271
Well... I... I...

413
00:22:09,439 --> 00:22:10,918
All I meantwas...

414
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,148
Oh, God.

415
00:22:28,679 --> 00:22:31,034
He quotes me, word forword:

416
00:22:31,479 --> 00:22:34,152
"Of course there will be
redundancies. Lots!"

417
00:22:34,599 --> 00:22:36,351
I'm most terribly sorry.

418
00:22:36,519 --> 00:22:39,079
