441
00:24:24,239 --> 00:24:27,629
Mr. Hacker, you look
as if you need some champagne.

442
00:24:27,919 --> 00:24:29,511
I do. Lots!

443
00:25:34,679 --> 00:25:35,714
Mr. Hacker?

444
00:25:37,759 --> 00:25:38,759
Hello.

445
00:25:40,279 --> 00:25:41,712
Thanks, mate.

446
00:25:44,719 --> 00:25:46,118
Gutterpress!

447
00:25:52,079 --> 00:25:54,229
All right, what do they say?

448
00:25:55,519 --> 00:25:59,148
"Mr. Economyfalls down in gutter
afterchampagne party".

449
00:25:59,319 --> 00:26:01,514
- Oh, my God!
- This one is better.

450
00:26:01,679 --> 00:26:04,147
"Hackertired and emotional
after Embassy reception".

451
00:26:04,319 --> 00:26:06,833
- Is that better?
- It's different.

452
00:26:08,319 --> 00:26:11,709
Do any of them say anything other
than "tired and emotional"?

